Noncommercial Purposes
A noncommercial purpose is one that is not intended for or directed towards commercial advantage or monetary compensation. Noncommercial purposes include (by way of example, not limitation) personal use, academic research, teaching, public interest experimentation, and contributing to open source projects released under OSI-approved or FSF Free/Libre licenses.

